commit.message:
DynamoDB: query/scan secondary index fixes (#7555)

* DynamoDB: query/scan secondary index fixes

Recent logic added in 194088 to accommodate a missing start key
brain-damaged pagination because determination of previously-encountered
items was not implemented correctly for all use cases.

* Make sure comparisons are performed in the sense of `ScanIndexForward`
  (previously, this was assumed to be `True` -- the default -- and
  returned incorrect results when reverse sorting was requested)
* When querying/scanning a secondary index, make comparisons using the
  index attribute(s) instead of the primary table attribute(s)

This commit now passes my project's internal test suite, and also passes
all existing moto DynamoDB unit tests. I expect to add a commit with a
unit test that exercises a query with reverse sorting on a GSI with
different key attributes, which describes my application's unit test
that failed prior to this fix.

* DynamoDB: Add GSI unit test

This exercises failing corner case prior to this PR: performing query on
secondary index and reverse-sorting results

---------

Co-authored-by: Scott Bailey <scott.bailey@godaddy.com>
